``Wilder, 81''</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Film legend <PERSON> Billy </PERSON> <PERSON> Wilder </PERSON>, a six-time Oscar winner for such films as `` The Lost Weekend'' and `` The Apartment,'' on Monday night became the 25th recipient of the <ORGANIZATION> Motion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Picture </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Academy </ORGANIZATION>'s <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> <PERSON> G. </PERSON> <PERSON> Thalberg </PERSON> Award. The award goes to `` a creative producer whose body of work reflects a consistently high quality of motion picture production.'' It is given only when the <ORGANIZATION> Academy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Picture </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sciences </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Directors </ORGANIZATION> decides there is a deserving recipient. <PERSON> Wilder </PERSON>, 81, has had a movie career of nearly 60 years, during which he has been nominated for an Oscar 21 times. `` As I look back, I've lived a charmed life,'' <PERSON> Wilder </PERSON> said, after being honored by the audience with a standing ovation. <PERSON> Wilder </PERSON> recounted how he had left <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION> to escape the <ORGANIZATION> Nazis </ORGANIZATION>, and was granted a chance to stay in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> by a consular official in <LOCATION> Mexicali </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>, who asked <PERSON> Wilder </PERSON> what he did for a living. Upon hearing <PERSON> Wilder </PERSON> wrote movies, the official stamped his passport and said, `` Write some good ones. `` That was 54 years ago, I've tried ever since,'' <PERSON> Wilder </PERSON> said. In 1961, he became the first person to win three Oscars at once for producing, directing and co-writing on `` The Apartment,'' best picture for 1960. <PERSON> Wilder </PERSON>'s career began in <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> and continued after he fled the <ORGANIZATION> Nazis </ORGANIZATION> and came to the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> in 1933. His mother, grandmother and stepfather died at <LOCATION> Auschwitz </LOCATION>. When he arrived in <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION>, he spoke fewer than 100 words of English and took up residence in the ladies' room of the Chateau Marmont Hotel. <PERSON> Wilder </PERSON> won Academy Awards for both directing and co-writing `` The Lost Weekend'' in 1945. He won a screenwriting award for `` Sunset Boulevard'' along with <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Brackett </PERSON> and D.M. <PERSON> Marshman </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr </PERSON>. The Thalberg award has been presented 28 times, sometimes more than once to the same individual. <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> Spielberg </PERSON> received it last year. <PERSON> Darryl </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Zanuck </PERSON> won the award three times and <PERSON> Hal </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Wallis </PERSON> twice, meaning it has gone to 25 people since it was established in 1937. Rules now prohibit a person from receiving the award more than once. <PERSON> Thalberg </PERSON> was an MGM production chief who died at age 37 but left a legacy of elevating the artistic quality of film with such movies as `` The Good Earth'' and `` Romeo and <PERSON> Juliet </PERSON>.''
