<HEAD>Man Arrested in Brooklyn On Maryland Murder Charges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 28-year-old man wanted for five murders in <LOCATION> Maryland </LOCATION> has been arrested after being spotted on a television show on fugitives. <PERSON> Carl </PERSON> <PERSON> Dunstrum </PERSON> was arrested late Saturday using warrant murders issued by Prince <PERSON> George </PERSON>'s County in <LOCATION> Maryland </LOCATION>, said Sgt. <PERSON> Maurice </PERSON> <PERSON> Howard </PERSON>, a department spokesman. In addition to the five killings for which he was sought in <LOCATION> Maryland </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Dunstrum </PERSON> was being questioned by <LOCATION> Brooklyn </LOCATION> detectives in connection with a sixth killing in that borough, a department spokeswoman, Sgt. <PERSON> Diane </PERSON> <PERSON> Kubler </PERSON>, said Sunday. The <LOCATION> Brooklyn </LOCATION> victim was <PERSON> Patrick </PERSON> <PERSON> Ford </PERSON>, 17, who was found shot once in the head on Nov. 26, <PERSON> Kubler </PERSON> said. About 30 police raided the basement apartment where <PERSON> Dunstrum </PERSON> was staying Saturday evening. <PERSON> Dunstrum </PERSON> was recently featured on the Fox network television show `` <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s Most Wanted,'' and the show helped lead to his arrest, <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> said. He was one of three New Yorkers wanted in the execution-style slayings of of four men and a woman Jan. 22 at an apartment complex in <LOCATION> Landover </LOCATION>, Md. Police at the time said the slayings appeared to be drug related. One woman shot in the neck survived the attack.
