<HEAD>American Exhibit Draws 110,000 Visitors In Budapest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An 18-day `` American Design'' exhibit staged at the Museum of Arts and Crafts drew 110,000 people, the highest number of spectators ever to attend a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> exhibit in <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION>. The 250 artifacts presented were mostly everyday products ranging from household appliances to child-care items, from personal computers to farm tractors. A special unit dealt with objects of `` the motorized way of life'' and `` office work today.'' Exhibit manager <PERSON> Ursual </PERSON> <PERSON> Williams </PERSON> said the large turnout was due, in part, to heavy media coverage of the American product show, which closed Sunday. `` American Design'' will now travel to the cities of Miskolc in northern <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Kecskemet </LOCATION> in central <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> for 18-day stints each.
