<TEXT>
 A man upset over a failed relationship fatally shot his former girlfriend and her boyfriend before killing himself by shooting himself while fleeing in his car with police chasing, authorities said. <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Tachias </PERSON>, 24, apparently shot <PERSON> Tina </PERSON> <PERSON> Bates </PERSON> and 30-year-old <PERSON> Rudy </PERSON> <PERSON> Jasso </PERSON> early Sunday when Ms. <PERSON> Bates </PERSON> told <PERSON> Tachias </PERSON> she did n't want to see him anymore, said police spokeswoman <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Molina </PERSON> <PERSON> Mescall </PERSON>. <PERSON> Tachias </PERSON> placed the body of the 24-year-old Ms. <PERSON> Bates </PERSON> in his car and led police on a chase through southwest <LOCATION> Albuquerque </LOCATION>. He then shot himself in the chest and drove the car into a pole, Ms. <PERSON> Mescall </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Tachias </PERSON> was pronounced dead a short time later at the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mexico </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION>.
