member appointed by the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> secretary-general, one appointed by the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government, and one chosen by mutual consent. Although the accord does not specifically mention missions, the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> maintains its rules concerning the unhindered functioning of diplomats accredited to its headquarters in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> also apply to the missions of member nations and organizations with observer status. The <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> was granted non-voting observer status at the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> in 1974. It has maintained an office in <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> since then. Several weeks ago, the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> filed suit in <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> after the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> refused to close its office there. The <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> was expected to respond in the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> case today, and the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> was expected to file a brief supporting the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> position. The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> boycott of the World Court proceedings marks the second time in four years that the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration has refused to take part in one of its cases. The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government claimed the court had no authority to handle a complaint against it filed in 1984 by <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION> and boycotted the last 17 months of the proceedings in that case. The World Court ultimately ruled in favor of <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION>, and ordered the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to halt its support for the Contra rebels fighting <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION>'s Sandinista government.
