<LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>. In <LOCATION> India </LOCATION>, two people were killed and at least 100 others injured Monday when police clashed with mobs of students who tried to close shops in northern <LOCATION> Kashmir </LOCATION> state to show sympathy for the victims of the weekend explosion. The <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> India </ORGANIZATION> reported that the injured included 70 policemen. <LOCATION> India </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> have fought three wars, two of them over <LOCATION> Kashmir </LOCATION>. Some of the Moslems, who predominate in <LOCATION> Kashmir </LOCATION> state, want to unite with <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION>.
