<HEAD>Sikh Radicals Rule Out Talks, Except on Independence</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DEEPAK SHARMA</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>AMRITSAR, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Two Sikh extremist groups on Monday ruled out peace talks with the government unless they focus on the radicals' demand for an independent nation. Also Monday, police reported five more people killed in the 6-year-old guerrilla war for a Sikh homeland in the northern state of <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION>. Authorities have blamed Sikh extremists for killing nearly 700 people, mostly Hindus and moderate Sikhs, since the start of the year. The five-member <ORGANIZATION> Panthic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> and its 11-member <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Khalistan </ORGANIZATION>, a subgroup, said Monday that anyone who negotiated with the government and did not demand Sikh independence would be killed. `` No one will be allowed to negotiate with <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Delhi </LOCATION> for less than <LOCATION> Khalistan </LOCATION>,'' the <ORGANIZATION> Panthic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> said, using the name Sikh extremists have given to their would-be nation. `` The struggle for <LOCATION> Khalistan </LOCATION> is being fought in an organized manner, and whosoever comes between the Sikhs and <PERSON> Khalistan </PERSON> will be taken care of,'' the group announced in a statement at the <ORGANIZATION> Golden </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Temple </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Amritsar </LOCATION>, the holiest shrine for Sikhs. <PERSON> Jagar </PERSON> <PERSON> Singh </PERSON>, a spokesman for the groups, read their statements. Members of both the Panthic Committee, formed in 1986, and the Council of <LOCATION> Khalistan </LOCATION>, created in October, generally operate underground. Many of them are wanted on sedition and murder charges by the government. The <ORGANIZATION> Panthic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> claims it is the official voice of the <ORGANIZATION> Sikh </ORGANIZATION> separatists, and has rejecte