Italian lire, up from 1,241.75; and 1.2420 Canadian dollars, down from 1.2478 In <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, the dollar rose against the British pound It cost $ 1.87 to buy one pound, cheaper than $ 1.8755 late Friday. Gold opened in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> at a bid price of $ 450.40 a troy ounce and at midmorning, the city's five major bullion dealers fixed a recommended price of $ 450.15, both down from late Friday's bid of $ 451.50. In <LOCATION> Zurich </LOCATION>, the bid price was $ 449.80, up from $ 449.50 late Friday. Earlier, in <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION>, gold rose 84 cents to close at a bid $ 451.95. Silver was quoted in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> this morning at a bid price of $ 6.43 a troy ounce, down from Friday's $ 6.48.
