<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Emhart </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> has agreed to acquire <ORGANIZATION> Price </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pfister </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in a deal valued at about $ 215 million, it was announced Monday. Under a definitive merger pact approved by the board of directors of both companies, <ORGANIZATION> Emhart </ORGANIZATION> said it would purchase each of Price Pfister's 11.4 million outstanding common shares for about $ 18.50. The merger requires formal approval by a majority of Price Pfister's stockholders. Based in <LOCATION> Pacoima </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, Price Pfister manufactures conventional and decorative faucets, valves, and fittings. It has about 1,600 employees. Farmington-based <ORGANIZATION> Emhart </ORGANIZATION> is a diversified, multinational producer of industrial and consumer products, and a provider of information and electronic systems technology services for the government and commercial markets.
